OL,6,FIn November this year, Whitelock was
OL,7,Fconvicted of murdering Ms Buckney by a
OL,8,Fjury who deliberated for around 30
OL,9,Fminutes following a two-week-long
OL,10,Ftrial.
OL,12,FFollowing the guilty verdict,
OL,13,FWhitelock shouted at the jury from the
OL,14,Fdock and had to be escorted from the
OL,15,Fcourtroom.
OL,17,FAhead of Whitelock's outburst, Mr
OL,18,FJustice Griffiths had asked if he
OL,19,Fwanted a barrister to represent him
OL,20,Fduring the sentencing.
