OL,6,FHe added: "You will also hear evidence
OL,7,Fof sexual assault upon her ` whether
OL,8,Fthis was done by the defendant before,
OL,9,Fduring or after his attack upon her is
OL,10,Fimpossible, forensically, to say."
OL,12,FWhitelock, of Tanycoed Road, Clydach,
OL,13,Frepresented himself during the trial
OL,14,Fand told jurors he had no memory of
OL,15,Fthe incident and was suffering from a
OL,16,Fbrain injury at the time after he
OL,17,Fslipped over while out fishing.
