OL,6,FDuring his closing arguments, Mr Rees
OL,7,Fdescribed to the jury how Whitelock
OL,8,Fhad gone to Ms Buckney's flat fully
OL,9,Fclothed, but the next time a neighbour
OL,10,Fsaw him he was covered in blood,
OL,11,Fwearing just his pants inside out.
OL,13,FJeffrey Llewelyn, a neighbour,
OL,14,Fconfronted Whitelock outside Ms
OL,15,FBuckney's house while he was kneeling
OL,16,Fon the front lawn and wiping dirt over
OL,17,Fhis body, where he heard the defendant
OL,18,Fsay "I've killed Wendy".
OL,20,FCredit: South Wales Police
